WEBVTT

00:00:02.440 --> 00:00:04.192
- <i>Previously on</i> The O. C:
- She came back...

00:00:04.360 --> 00:00:05.634
...so I guess you're going home.

00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:08.030
- You're his mother.
- I'm a mess, not a mother.

00:00:08.200 --> 00:00:11.749
- You can't walk away.
- This way he ends up with a real mom.

00:00:12.760 --> 00:00:14.716
It's sweet that
you're concerned about this boy...

00:00:14.880 --> 00:00:17.189
...but you need to focus on the future,
which means Luke.

00:00:17.360 --> 00:00:18.998
She chose you.
You're the one she wants.

00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:21.071
- I wanna sail to Tahiti.
- You're taking this to Tahiti?

00:00:21.240 --> 00:00:22.753
- How much do you need?
- It's $100,000.

00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:25.798
The check that you guys gave Jimmy.
We needed that 100 grand.

00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:27.916
- Ryan's gonna stay with us now.
- Awesome.

00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:30.355
We just got in way over our heads.

00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:38.073
- Oh, really? You think so?
- I do.

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:39.798
We'll see about that, monkey pox.

00:00:42.480 --> 00:00:44.710
So the pupil has become the teacher.

00:00:44.880 --> 00:00:47.872
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

00:00:48.240 --> 00:00:49.389
Who died?

00:00:49.560 --> 00:00:51.915
Seth, we need to talk to Ryan.

00:00:52.520 --> 00:00:53.999
Okay.

00:00:54.160 --> 00:00:58.153
If this has to do with the rug, I want to
say that Ryan had nothing to do with it.

00:00:58.320 --> 00:00:59.719
What about the rug?

00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:01.678
I'm gonna go now.

00:01:06.640 --> 00:01:08.073
So...

00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:11.948
Kirsten and I went
to Child Services this morning...

00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:15.749
...and we told them
that we want you to stay with us.

00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:19.794
But there's a catch.
Because you're a minor...

00:01:19.960 --> 00:01:22.349
...the only way they're gonna
allow that to happen...

00:01:22.520 --> 00:01:25.637
...is if we assume
all legal responsibility for you.

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:31.557
- I can't ask you guys to do that.
- You don't have to. We're asking you.

00:01:31.720 --> 00:01:35.315
We've all talked about it,
and we want to be your legal guardians.

00:01:36.040 --> 00:01:38.031
We want you to be part of the family.

00:01:38.560 --> 00:01:39.629
If you wanna be.

00:01:41.640 --> 00:01:42.914
What if it doesn't work?

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:45.513
Well, how do you mean?

00:01:46.520 --> 00:01:49.671
What if something happens
and you guys change your mind?

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:51.319
Like what?

00:01:51.480 --> 00:01:53.391
You steal a car?
You burn down a house?

00:01:53.560 --> 00:01:56.120
You beat up the captain
of the water polo team?

00:01:56.280 --> 00:01:58.191
Those ships have sailed, my friend.

00:01:58.360 --> 00:02:02.592
You have to promise us you'll stay out
of trouble. From now on, no more fights.

00:02:02.760 --> 00:02:08.153
You're still on probation, and Child
Services will be up our ass all the time.

00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:12.273
No more trouble. I promise.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:16.228
Well...

00:02:19.800 --> 00:02:23.315
- Welcome to the family.
- Thanks, guys.

00:02:28.640 --> 00:02:30.995
Okay, Seth. You can come out now.

00:02:35.720 --> 00:02:37.711
You knew about this
and didn't say anything.

00:02:37.880 --> 00:02:39.154
I didn't wanna jinx it.

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:41.875
Dude, you're a Cohen now.

00:02:42.040 --> 00:02:45.191
Welcome to a life of insecurity
and paralyzing self-doubt.

00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:49.478
Yeah. Now all I have to do
is stay out of trouble.

00:02:50.840 --> 00:02:52.512
Yeah, that could be...

00:02:52.680 --> 00:02:54.033
...difficult.

00:03:28.680 --> 00:03:32.309
You're gonna need
bedding and towels.

00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:36.074
How's the bed, Ryan?
Is it comfortable?

00:03:36.760 --> 00:03:38.034
Yeah, it's...

00:03:41.320 --> 00:03:43.311
It's fine. It's great.

00:03:44.280 --> 00:03:47.636
We want you to have your privacy,
but it's a pool house. It needs warmth.

00:03:47.800 --> 00:03:50.633
You'll need chairs and a desk,
a bookshelf...

00:03:50.800 --> 00:03:53.553
Plasma flat screen,
a couple of turntables, minibar.

00:03:53.760 --> 00:03:57.594
And we should clean all this out so that
you have room for some of your...

00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:02.233
Right, you don't have stuff, so we have
to buy clothes, shoes and underpants.

00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:04.391
Mom, don't say "underpants."

00:04:05.400 --> 00:04:07.118
I've got everything I need. Really.

00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:10.397
I bet you don't have a tux.
Because you're gonna need one.

00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:12.758
- For what?
- For cotillion.

00:04:12.920 --> 00:04:16.117
It's the annual debutante ball.
It's Newport's biggest event.

00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:17.554
Until whatever's next week.

00:04:17.720 --> 00:04:20.439
It's the day when Newport's
most accomplished young women...

00:04:20.600 --> 00:04:22.113
...make their debut into society.

00:04:22.280 --> 00:04:24.874
Or another excuse for them
to get wasted and throw up.

00:04:25.040 --> 00:04:28.794
I was a deb. I made my debut at this
very country club not so many years ago.

00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:31.713
- The year was...
- Hey, watch it.

00:04:34.560 --> 00:04:36.039
You know what?

00:04:37.480 --> 00:04:39.914
- Maybe I should skip it.
- You have to go.

00:04:40.080 --> 00:04:42.594
It's a family tradition.
And you're part of the family.

00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:44.910
- Hello, dear.
- Hi, Peggy.

00:04:45.080 --> 00:04:46.832
- How are you?
- I'm good.

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.434
- How's it going?
- It will be fine.

00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:52.990
- The fitting area's back there.
- Thank you.

00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:55.196
Come on, boys. It'll be fun.

00:05:07.680 --> 00:05:09.113
Sandy.

00:05:09.280 --> 00:05:10.713
Hey, Jimmy.

00:05:11.840 --> 00:05:13.592
Got some surfing in, huh?

00:05:13.760 --> 00:05:16.558
Late court date. Gotta take advantage.

00:05:16.720 --> 00:05:18.711
I used to have hobbies.

00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:21.838
Look, I know you're not thrilled
with me.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:26.073
When I borrowed the money from
Kirsten, I should have asked you.

00:05:26.240 --> 00:05:29.471
- I wasn't going behind your back.
- Look, it's done. Let's move on.

00:05:29.640 --> 00:05:32.029
I was afraid of what you'd think of me.

00:05:33.440 --> 00:05:35.032
Losing as much money as I have...

00:05:36.760 --> 00:05:38.876
...is not an impressive accomplishment.

00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:42.191
- How much money did you lose?
- Look...

00:05:42.480 --> 00:05:43.595
It's not important.

00:05:45.760 --> 00:05:47.830
- How'd you lose it?
- The important thing is...

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.630
...I don't know what Julie and I would
do without friends like you and Kirsten.

00:05:54.720 --> 00:05:55.914
So everything's okay?

00:05:56.080 --> 00:05:58.594
Oh, yeah. Yeah. Thank you.

00:05:58.760 --> 00:06:00.910
- I'll see you around.
- See you.

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:09.676
Okay, pick whatever you want.
We have Gucci, Armani. Versace's there.

00:06:15.760 --> 00:06:18.433
Hi, I'm picking up for Marissa Cooper.

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:20.989
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:23.358
What are you doing here?

00:06:23.520 --> 00:06:24.999
I...

00:06:25.160 --> 00:06:27.276
...had an appointment
with my personal shopper.

00:06:28.640 --> 00:06:31.313
But I thought you said
you were leaving with your mom.

00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:36.113
It didn't really work out,
so I'm kind of living with the Cohens.

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:39.309
- For good?
- Is that...

00:06:39.480 --> 00:06:41.835
...gonna be a problem?
- No, no. It's great.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:44.036
I mean, I guess now
we can be friends, right?

00:06:46.080 --> 00:06:47.354
Hey, Coop.

00:06:47.520 --> 00:06:50.478
These gloves are giving me
serious sausage arms.

00:06:50.640 --> 00:06:53.712
What are you still doing here?
I thought you were going back to Chino.

00:06:53.880 --> 00:06:56.348
- I had a change of plans.
- Ryan's living here now.

00:06:57.320 --> 00:06:59.595
- He's what?
- Look, I'm not here to cause problems.

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:01.159
Is everything all right?

00:07:03.320 --> 00:07:05.038
- I'll be in the truck.
- Great.

00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:09.071
Marissa, I was gonna call you.
Since you're lead deb...

00:07:09.240 --> 00:07:10.798
Seth?

00:07:10.960 --> 00:07:13.474
I wanted to introduce you
to a couple of white knights.

00:07:13.640 --> 00:07:16.074
In case any of your girls
needed a last-minute escort.

00:07:16.240 --> 00:07:18.674
- Okay.
- Every girl needs a white knight.

00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:22.235
Seth Cohen, white knight.

00:07:23.880 --> 00:07:26.519
So you'll be at the rehearsal?

00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:28.432
Yes, absolutely.

00:07:29.400 --> 00:07:31.038
See you then.

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:33.439
Bye.

00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:35.670
Cotillion rocks.

00:07:36.320 --> 00:07:40.233
You want me to fix you up with Ryan?
I thought you said he was a "psycho."

00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:43.278
- That was before I got to know him.
- When did you get to know him?

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:44.589
Just now.

00:07:44.760 --> 00:07:46.876
Plus there's that
whole brooding bad-boy thing.

00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:49.110
He's wounded. I can save him.

00:07:49.280 --> 00:07:52.511
Have you ever really talked to him?
He's not really a bad boy.

00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:55.194
Well, he will be by the time
I get through with him.

00:07:58.720 --> 00:08:02.395
What? You're not, like,
into him, are you?

00:08:02.560 --> 00:08:04.915
- I mean, you're with Luke, right?
- Right.

00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:06.399
Good.

00:08:09.600 --> 00:08:11.272
Sandy Cohen?

00:08:11.440 --> 00:08:15.274
I'm with the Securities and Exchange
Commission, Enforcement Division.

00:08:16.360 --> 00:08:17.793
Okay.

00:08:17.960 --> 00:08:20.315
I was hoping you could help me out
with a case.

00:08:20.840 --> 00:08:23.035
Sure. What can I do for you?

00:08:23.400 --> 00:08:26.392
Were you aware, Mr. Cohen,
that a check your wife made out...

00:08:26.560 --> 00:08:30.712
...to a James Cooper for $100,000
was not treated as an investment...

00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:33.110
...but as a deposit
into his personal account?

00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:37.239
It wasn't an investment. It was a loan.
My wife and Jimmy are old...

00:08:38.400 --> 00:08:40.675
- What's this about?
- Did you know Mr. Cooper is...

00:08:40.840 --> 00:08:43.308
...the subject of an
SEC fraud investigation?

00:08:44.440 --> 00:08:45.873
No.

00:08:47.120 --> 00:08:48.599
No, I didn't.

00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:54.277
Hey. White gloves,
ready for a comeback.

00:08:54.440 --> 00:08:56.635
Hey. What are you doing home?

00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:00.511
Fellas, do you mind?

00:09:01.760 --> 00:09:04.513
- Lf this is about the vase...
- Which vase?

00:09:05.160 --> 00:09:08.789
Nothing. Let's go, Ryan.
Come on, buddy.

00:09:14.880 --> 00:09:16.074
What's going on?

00:09:18.240 --> 00:09:20.470
Okay. So...

00:09:20.800 --> 00:09:22.791
I think I'm not going to cotillion.

00:09:22.960 --> 00:09:24.678
Yeah, okay. Except that you are.

00:09:24.840 --> 00:09:27.877
I made a promise to your parents
that I'd stay out of trouble.

00:09:28.040 --> 00:09:30.429
It's a debutante ball.
What trouble can you get into?

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:31.953
Why don't you ask Luke.

00:09:32.520 --> 00:09:34.670
Ryan, we're white knights, okay?

00:09:34.840 --> 00:09:37.877
That means Marissa probably
already has some sad, Ionely girl...

00:09:38.040 --> 00:09:41.237
...lined up for you to escort,
so you can't cancel at the last minute.

00:09:41.400 --> 00:09:43.038
That's a faux pas, buddy.

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.474
- Would you call her?
- No.

00:09:49.640 --> 00:09:53.918
If you're gonna bail on Marissa and some
poor, pathetic, dateless girl...

00:09:54.080 --> 00:09:56.310
...you'll just have to
do that one yourself.

00:09:56.840 --> 00:09:58.273
Are you sure?

00:09:58.440 --> 00:10:01.876
These guys say Jimmy's been siphoning
money out of his clients' accounts...

00:10:02.040 --> 00:10:03.837
...to cover his own debts.

00:10:05.440 --> 00:10:09.274
- How could we not know this?
- Because we trusted him. Everybody did.

00:10:09.440 --> 00:10:12.796
This entire community wrote him blank
checks. You gave him 100 grand.

00:10:12.960 --> 00:10:14.188
It was just a loan.

00:10:14.360 --> 00:10:17.591
Which, according to the SEC,
makes us worth investigating too.

00:10:17.760 --> 00:10:19.671
I'm gonna be sick.

00:10:22.880 --> 00:10:25.155
I'm gonna have to call our friends
and let them know.

00:10:25.320 --> 00:10:28.551
Sandy, wait.
You're just gonna panic people.

00:10:28.720 --> 00:10:31.029
Don't do anything
until I talk to him, okay?

00:10:31.200 --> 00:10:33.873
Put your feelings for him aside.
Forget about your history.

00:10:34.040 --> 00:10:36.190
He's one of my oldest friends.

00:10:38.840 --> 00:10:41.400
If it's true, I just need
to hear it from him.

00:10:43.880 --> 00:10:45.074
<i>I'm coming.</i>

00:10:47.080 --> 00:10:49.355
Hey. You're...

00:10:49.520 --> 00:10:51.112
...at my house.
- I...

00:10:51.280 --> 00:10:53.794
Well, I wanted to talk to you
about cotillion.

00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:55.678
Oh. Okay, well...

00:10:55.840 --> 00:10:59.992
I was just trying this on,
and I can't seem to reach the...

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:01.479
Did you want me to...?

00:11:02.560 --> 00:11:04.312
I could... Do you want me to...?

00:11:04.760 --> 00:11:08.070
Yeah. You know, actually,
if you wouldn't mind.

00:11:32.240 --> 00:11:33.753
Thanks.

00:11:34.440 --> 00:11:36.317
So, what's up with cotillion?

00:11:37.760 --> 00:11:39.876
What time did you want me there?

00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:46.596
I'm... I'm so sorry.

00:11:46.760 --> 00:11:49.513
I never meant for you
to be dragged in like this.

00:11:49.680 --> 00:11:54.390
How did this happen? I understand
a couple of bad investments, but theft?

00:11:54.560 --> 00:11:57.028
- Theft? No, no.
- Okay, honey, so we're gonna...

00:11:57.200 --> 00:11:58.918
- Oh, Kirsten.
- Julie.

00:11:59.360 --> 00:12:03.672
- Jimmy didn't say you were coming by.
- She just had a quick business question.

00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:06.115
- A quickie, huh?
- Julie.

00:12:06.280 --> 00:12:09.590
I'm kidding. So we're off.
Kaitlin needs new shoes for cotillion.

00:12:09.760 --> 00:12:13.275
Then we're test-driving the CLK, then I
have to re-up Marissa's tennis lessons.

00:12:13.440 --> 00:12:15.795
- So which credit card should I use?
- The MasterCard.

00:12:15.960 --> 00:12:19.316
- What about the Amex?
- No, don't use the Amex. The...

00:12:19.480 --> 00:12:20.833
Get the miles.

00:12:22.120 --> 00:12:23.519
Okay.

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:25.513
You two have fun.

00:12:27.640 --> 00:12:31.679
Well, now that the how and why
have been accounted for...

00:12:31.840 --> 00:12:36.868
Look, I was not stealing.
I was borrowing to pay back my debts.

00:12:37.040 --> 00:12:39.349
And then the market took a turn,
and there we are.

00:12:39.520 --> 00:12:40.999
You were stealing.

00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:46.518
I... I can't say no to my family.
I'll pay everything back.

00:12:46.680 --> 00:12:49.956
- I just need that one stock. That one.
- Jimmy, you need help.

00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:57.595
Yeah, well, who's gonna help me?

00:13:02.400 --> 00:13:05.312
So, what exactly happens
at this rehearsal?

00:13:05.480 --> 00:13:07.630
Just stupid cotillion stuff.

00:13:07.800 --> 00:13:10.314
Bowing and curtsying.

00:13:10.480 --> 00:13:13.870
One, two, three. One, two, three.

00:13:14.040 --> 00:13:17.237
Try to enjoy this, please.

00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:19.755
Dancing? You didn't tell me
there was dancing.

00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:22.832
Well, if I'd told you there was dancing,
I'd be here by myself.

00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:24.479
Because I really...

00:13:24.640 --> 00:13:26.039
...don't dance.

00:13:26.200 --> 00:13:28.191
Neither do I. I just move well.

00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:33.110
Want me to teach you that one?

00:13:34.160 --> 00:13:37.038
- Maybe later. You ready?
- Take your places.

00:13:38.400 --> 00:13:41.437
Hey, guys.
So can I introduce you to your debs?

00:13:41.600 --> 00:13:43.238
We've already met.

00:13:43.560 --> 00:13:47.030
Oh, well, actually, Summer, Ryan's
already been promised to someone else.

00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:49.077
You gave him to someone else?

00:13:49.240 --> 00:13:53.074
Who? Who's pathetic enough not
to have a date the day before cotillion?

00:13:53.240 --> 00:13:56.198
Actually, at this point,
that would be you.

00:13:56.360 --> 00:14:00.319
So, Anna Stern, this is Ryan Atwood.
Anna just moved here from Pittsburgh.

00:14:00.480 --> 00:14:02.072
Pittsburgh?

00:14:03.080 --> 00:14:05.389
Can we just get this over with?

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:09.752
<i>Caliente.</i>

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:14.837
- Hey, it's not that bad.
- You haven't seen me dance.

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:16.752
Well, I can help you.

00:14:16.920 --> 00:14:19.480
So, like, what am I supposed to do?

00:14:19.640 --> 00:14:21.392
Over here.

00:14:23.200 --> 00:14:24.679
Fine. Let's go.

00:14:24.840 --> 00:14:26.910
Are you sure? Because if you're not...

00:14:27.080 --> 00:14:29.594
Just don't talk to me.

00:14:29.760 --> 00:14:33.116
All right, I get it. Our...
Our connection's deeper than words.

00:14:35.800 --> 00:14:38.951
That's it. I'm done. I'm sorry.
Chock-full of quiet now.

00:14:42.520 --> 00:14:44.511
Okay. So you guys will be over here.

00:14:44.680 --> 00:14:47.148
If you want to,
go ahead and get into waltz position.

00:14:49.200 --> 00:14:52.636
Which means, Anna, you put
your left hand on Ryan's shoulder.

00:14:54.680 --> 00:14:57.069
No, not like that. Here, watch.

00:14:59.200 --> 00:15:02.715
Okay? Now, Ryan, you put
your right hand on my back.

00:15:03.280 --> 00:15:04.952
Lower.

00:15:24.320 --> 00:15:26.231
Okay. Good.

00:15:26.720 --> 00:15:27.914
Good.

00:15:28.080 --> 00:15:29.718
I'd be pretty jealous right now...

00:15:31.000 --> 00:15:32.479
...if Chino wasn't gay.

00:15:33.320 --> 00:15:35.072
- Luke.
- What? No, it doesn't bother me.

00:15:35.240 --> 00:15:36.514
He was born that way, right?

00:15:36.680 --> 00:15:38.716
Thanks. I think
we can take it from here.

00:15:38.880 --> 00:15:40.552
Okay.

00:15:44.720 --> 00:15:45.835
You're into her, huh?

00:15:47.320 --> 00:15:49.117
Man, are you in trouble.

00:15:49.840 --> 00:15:51.398
- I know.
- Yeah.

00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:52.959
- Yeah.
- Come on.

00:15:57.520 --> 00:15:59.431
All right, darlings, listen up.

00:15:59.600 --> 00:16:03.036
Let's review the classic waltz step.
Phillip?

00:16:03.840 --> 00:16:05.273
And...

00:16:05.440 --> 00:16:06.793
One, two, three.

00:16:06.960 --> 00:16:08.313
One, two, three.

00:16:08.480 --> 00:16:10.038
One, two, three.

00:16:10.200 --> 00:16:12.270
One, two, three. Smile, please.

00:16:12.440 --> 00:16:16.319
- That kid is stalking you.
- He is not. He's my neighbor.

00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:18.675
And he's not going anywhere,
so get used to him.

00:16:18.840 --> 00:16:23.356
What I'll never get used to is that kid
macking on you when I turn my back.

00:16:23.520 --> 00:16:25.670
So you don't trust me?

00:16:26.560 --> 00:16:28.118
No, I...

00:16:29.400 --> 00:16:33.359
I don't trust anybody else.
Not around you.

00:16:38.680 --> 00:16:40.557
- Wait.
- Slow down.

00:16:40.720 --> 00:16:43.188
Are you the kid from Chino
who steals cars...

00:16:43.360 --> 00:16:45.669
...and sets people's houses on fire?

00:16:47.640 --> 00:16:51.679
You're saying I'm making my debut into
society with Newport's most wanted?

00:16:51.840 --> 00:16:54.149
- Is that gonna be a problem?
- I can't wait.

00:16:57.960 --> 00:16:59.837
Absolutely not.

00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:04.278
As happy as I am that you came all
the way out to my office to visit me...

00:17:05.360 --> 00:17:06.395
...the answer is no.

00:17:06.560 --> 00:17:10.394
Corey! I need that file
on <i>Nerodner v. Caplin.</i>

00:17:10.560 --> 00:17:13.154
- And I need the INS report on my 4:30.
- Yes, sir.

00:17:13.320 --> 00:17:16.073
I got a two-time drug offender
they want to deport. 15 years old.

00:17:16.240 --> 00:17:17.832
Sandy, he needs help.

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:21.197
Jimmy Cooper? He stole from his clients,
he stole from his friends...

00:17:21.360 --> 00:17:25.433
...and then he had the nerve to borrow
$100,000 from us to cover it up.

00:17:25.600 --> 00:17:27.909
He was trying to provide for his family.

00:17:28.080 --> 00:17:29.479
Yeah. Boats, ponies...

00:17:29.640 --> 00:17:32.108
- You'll defend a drug offender, but...?
- Yes.

00:17:32.480 --> 00:17:36.792
My clients are kids who have
no hope, no guidance, nothing.

00:17:36.960 --> 00:17:40.396
Jimmy Cooper is just another
spoiled Newport brat...

00:17:40.560 --> 00:17:42.198
...who had everything handed to him.

00:17:42.360 --> 00:17:44.635
- Like me.
- No. Not like you.

00:17:44.800 --> 00:17:47.792
You would never lie.
You would never steal.

00:17:47.960 --> 00:17:50.030
I'd like to think that, but the truth is...

00:17:50.200 --> 00:17:53.078
...there isn't anything
that I wouldn't do for my family.

00:17:53.600 --> 00:17:55.158
See you at home.

00:18:00.200 --> 00:18:03.431
- Three hours of dancing.
- I feel like I could go for three more.

00:18:03.600 --> 00:18:05.477
Ryan. So Anna seemed nice.

00:18:05.640 --> 00:18:08.154
I mean, I just figured she's new
and you're new, so...

00:18:08.320 --> 00:18:12.074
- Yeah.
- Great. Good.

00:18:12.840 --> 00:18:15.434
Holl, I was about to tell them
about the cookout tonight.

00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:17.955
It's at my house.
I do it every year for cotillion.

00:18:18.120 --> 00:18:20.714
- You didn't do it last year.
- Yeah, we did.

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:23.709
Ouch.

00:18:23.880 --> 00:18:25.108
- See you tonight.
- Bye.

00:18:25.280 --> 00:18:26.599
See you there.

00:18:26.760 --> 00:18:28.955
You really think
that's such a great idea?

00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:31.679
Yeah, I do.

00:18:31.840 --> 00:18:35.913
You're living here now, and there's no
reason why we all can't hang out, right?

00:18:38.400 --> 00:18:41.073
- I can think of a reason.
- Yeah. I'm not going.

00:18:41.240 --> 00:18:43.470
- I don't want to go alone.
- Summer will be there.

00:18:43.640 --> 00:18:47.030
Yeah, I'm still going. I would just prefer
not to go alone. Listen to me.

00:18:47.200 --> 00:18:51.034
We're like brothers now, okay?
That means we do stuff for each other.

00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:54.749
If you do this for me, later on
I'll be able to do something for you.

00:18:54.920 --> 00:18:58.276
I don't know what it's going to be yet,
but it's gonna be awesome.

00:18:58.640 --> 00:18:59.629
Please?

00:18:59.800 --> 00:19:02.758
Okay, here we are.
Thank you very much. Okay.

00:19:02.920 --> 00:19:06.276
Here we go, sweetheart.
Make sure we got everything.

00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:09.750
Hey, Jimmy Cooper.
Just the man I wanted to see.

00:19:09.920 --> 00:19:12.150
- Hey, Greg. Hey, Holly.
- Hey, Mr. Cooper.

00:19:12.320 --> 00:19:13.514
Somebody's having a party.

00:19:13.680 --> 00:19:16.319
Holly's hosting this thing for the debs
out at the beach house.

00:19:16.480 --> 00:19:19.278
That's right. Marissa's going.
Have a good time.

00:19:19.440 --> 00:19:22.238
Honey, take these down to the car.
I'll be right there. Okay?

00:19:22.400 --> 00:19:24.994
Hi, I'm picking up for Cooper.

00:19:25.160 --> 00:19:28.357
Listen, Jimmy. I haven't heard back
from you. Did you get my messages?

00:19:28.520 --> 00:19:29.589
Yeah, I'm sorry.

00:19:29.760 --> 00:19:32.991
You know, work has been so crazy.
But what's going on?

00:19:33.160 --> 00:19:36.038
I've been asked to invest
in a commercial real-estate property.

00:19:36.200 --> 00:19:38.077
It could be a nice second income for us.

00:19:38.240 --> 00:19:41.596
It might be our only income, the way
the pharmaceutical industry's going.

00:19:41.760 --> 00:19:44.149
- That sounds promising.
- Yeah.

00:19:44.320 --> 00:19:48.393
So we're gonna have to pull $250,000
out of the investment account.

00:19:50.720 --> 00:19:54.235
Are you sure you wanna do that,
with the market about to turn around?

00:19:54.400 --> 00:19:58.632
Sir? I'm sorry,
but your credit card's been declined.

00:20:01.760 --> 00:20:05.469
Oh, it's a new card,
and I forgot to activate it.

00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:07.471
Did you want to use another card?

00:20:08.400 --> 00:20:10.231
Dad, I'm gonna be late
to my own party.

00:20:10.400 --> 00:20:11.594
Okay, honey.

00:20:11.760 --> 00:20:15.639
I'll call you tomorrow about the details.
Just bring the check to the cotillion.

00:20:15.800 --> 00:20:17.279
Enjoy your meal.

00:20:21.480 --> 00:20:23.835
I'll just pay with cash.

00:20:28.800 --> 00:20:31.030
Give me 10 minutes to find Summer,
lock it down for tomorrow.

00:20:31.200 --> 00:20:32.315
See where the night takes me.

00:20:32.480 --> 00:20:35.074
- Better take you back here in 10 minutes.
- Don't wait up.

00:20:35.240 --> 00:20:38.437
Come on. Two Jack Johnson tickets,
a massage at Burke Williams...

00:20:38.600 --> 00:20:42.832
...and all the money I have on me,
which is $11.

00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:45.355
Sorry, Summer,
I don't want to trade escorts.

00:20:46.400 --> 00:20:49.472
- Hey, Summer.
- What did I say about talking to me?

00:20:49.640 --> 00:20:54.555
Okay. I just wanted to make sure
we're still on for tomorrow night.

00:20:54.720 --> 00:20:56.199
I guess.

00:20:56.360 --> 00:20:59.670
Could you even pretend
to be a little bit stoked?

00:21:00.480 --> 00:21:02.118
Fair enough.

00:21:02.280 --> 00:21:05.556
You're a really good barbecue-tionist.

00:21:11.120 --> 00:21:12.599
There it is.

00:21:14.000 --> 00:21:15.672
Oh, jeez!

00:21:19.320 --> 00:21:22.073
You lost a bet. You lost a bet.
You've got to pay up.

00:21:33.800 --> 00:21:35.518
You sure you want to be seen with me?

00:21:35.680 --> 00:21:40.196
Hey, I'm glad you came. I mean,
how could you possibly miss all this?

00:21:43.840 --> 00:21:47.037
- I'm gonna go.
- Hey, we're not doing anything wrong.

00:21:47.200 --> 00:21:50.909
Well, now that you've moved in, I see
you're making yourself right at home.

00:21:51.080 --> 00:21:53.116
Luke, come on.
You said you were gonna try.

00:21:53.280 --> 00:21:57.432
I'm trying. I'm trying to understand
why there's all these people here...

00:21:57.600 --> 00:22:01.115
...and you only want to talk to her.
- Hey, I wanted to talk to him.

00:22:01.280 --> 00:22:04.716
Look, babe, why don't you go talk
to Summer, all right? She looks Ionely.

00:22:04.880 --> 00:22:07.348
Or you can,
and I'll finish talking to Ryan.

00:22:09.000 --> 00:22:11.150
No, it's okay. I'm just gonna go.

00:22:11.320 --> 00:22:13.788
- No. Stay.
- What are you doing? Don't tell him that.

00:22:13.960 --> 00:22:17.270
- Don't tell her what to do.
- I thought you were leaving.

00:22:17.440 --> 00:22:19.351
Why don't I just help you out.

00:22:22.880 --> 00:22:24.279
I'm not gonna fight.

00:22:26.920 --> 00:22:29.150
- Even if I do this?
- Luke!

00:22:30.200 --> 00:22:32.031
Oh, God. Are you okay?

00:22:33.600 --> 00:22:35.830
God, Luke, you're such an idiot.

00:22:37.080 --> 00:22:41.596
You just got your butt kicked and didn't
fight back. Dude, you really are a Cohen.

00:22:41.760 --> 00:22:43.352
Yeah. Let's get you home.

00:22:55.600 --> 00:22:57.830
What are you doing?
Why aren't you dressed yet?

00:22:58.000 --> 00:23:01.231
I'm not going. Would you let Anna know?
She'll probably be relieved.

00:23:01.400 --> 00:23:03.595
Are you not going
because you're afraid of Luke?

00:23:03.760 --> 00:23:05.955
That's not what I'm afraid of.

00:23:07.560 --> 00:23:11.872
Look, your parents taking me in is the
greatest thing that's happened to me.

00:23:12.040 --> 00:23:14.793
I'm not gonna lose it
just to kick some guy's ass.

00:23:15.960 --> 00:23:18.474
- You could totally kick his ass, right?
- Oh, yeah.

00:23:18.640 --> 00:23:20.039
Cool.

00:23:21.640 --> 00:23:23.915
All right. Well...

00:23:25.240 --> 00:23:26.753
...have fun.

00:23:30.680 --> 00:23:33.433
Sweetie, I need to borrow
your lip gloss.

00:23:33.600 --> 00:23:36.239
Oh, I love this dress.

00:23:36.400 --> 00:23:38.789
Really? Maybe you should wear it.

00:23:38.960 --> 00:23:43.317
You're sweet, but I think we both know
I'm no longer a size 0.

00:23:43.480 --> 00:23:45.789
Give me a few more months
on the Zone.

00:23:45.960 --> 00:23:48.076
I don't think I want to go.

00:23:48.240 --> 00:23:51.789
I'm sorry, I thought I heard you say you
don't want to go to your own cotillion.

00:23:51.960 --> 00:23:54.428
Look, Luke and I
got in a fight last night, okay?

00:23:54.600 --> 00:23:56.909
So you got into a fight.
You've had fights before.

00:23:57.080 --> 00:23:58.798
You guys have been together forever.

00:23:58.960 --> 00:24:01.315
Maybe that's the problem.

00:24:02.600 --> 00:24:05.751
I mean, what if
there's someone else out there?

00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:08.036
Like who? That boy from Chino?

00:24:11.520 --> 00:24:15.354
Do you want to end up like Aunt Cindy,
with four kids in a trailer park?

00:24:15.520 --> 00:24:17.317
She broke my mom's heart.
You won't break mine.

00:24:17.480 --> 00:24:20.597
- So now this is about you?
- No, sweetie, it's about you.

00:24:20.760 --> 00:24:23.797
- What future is there with that boy?
- Mom, I'm 16.

00:24:23.960 --> 00:24:27.475
The choices you make when you're 16
can affect your entire future.

00:24:27.640 --> 00:24:31.997
Luke is from a good family. If you stay
with him, you'll always be comfortable.

00:24:32.160 --> 00:24:35.789
- I'm comfortable now.
- Nothing in life is certain.

00:24:37.200 --> 00:24:39.919
- What does that mean?
- It means you'll put on this dress...

00:24:40.080 --> 00:24:44.198
...do your hair like I showed you and
make your debut into society with Luke.

00:24:44.360 --> 00:24:45.679
I can't.

00:24:48.240 --> 00:24:49.639
I'm sorry.

00:24:50.720 --> 00:24:51.789
No, you're not.

00:24:53.160 --> 00:24:55.310
But you will be.

00:25:02.120 --> 00:25:04.350
What are you doing?
Why aren't you dressed?

00:25:04.520 --> 00:25:06.909
- I'm not going.
- What do you mean, you're not going?

00:25:07.080 --> 00:25:08.911
I don't feel like getting dressed up...

00:25:09.080 --> 00:25:11.594
...and pretending Jimmy Cooper
is the O.C. Golden boy.

00:25:12.360 --> 00:25:16.194
And any community that makes that guy
a hero is not one I feel like being part of.

00:25:17.040 --> 00:25:18.189
You're not going either?

00:25:18.360 --> 00:25:21.079
- I wanted to leave 20 minutes ago.
- Let's go.

00:25:21.240 --> 00:25:24.038
- Dad, why aren't you...?
- Seth. Now.

00:25:26.640 --> 00:25:29.313
I don't know.
Maybe I shouldn't go either.

00:25:29.480 --> 00:25:32.677
What? What is wrong with this family?

00:25:32.840 --> 00:25:36.037
This is cotillion, the most
important event of the year.

00:25:36.200 --> 00:25:37.952
Am I the only one who gets it?

00:25:38.120 --> 00:25:39.872
I get it, Mommy.

00:25:40.040 --> 00:25:42.873
Daddy, it's Mr. Fisher again.
He's called, like, three times.

00:25:43.040 --> 00:25:46.157
No. We do not have time
for you two to talk business.

00:25:46.320 --> 00:25:50.074
Tell Greg Daddy will see him
at the cotillion. Right, Jimmy?

00:25:51.920 --> 00:25:53.990
All right.

00:25:54.160 --> 00:25:56.549
Come on. We don't wanna be late.

00:26:01.800 --> 00:26:03.711
You guys know Anna Stern?

00:26:03.880 --> 00:26:05.313
Seth.

00:26:07.120 --> 00:26:08.235
Wow.

00:26:09.720 --> 00:26:12.553
- You think?
- Yes...

00:26:12.720 --> 00:26:16.679
...I do. Which makes this
even harder to say.

00:26:16.840 --> 00:26:21.356
Anna, just know that, in life,
there are peaks and...

00:26:21.520 --> 00:26:23.033
Ryan's not coming, is he?

00:26:23.200 --> 00:26:25.998
Kind of took the wind
out of my sails there, but yes.

00:26:27.640 --> 00:26:30.279
- Are you okay?
- I'll survive.

00:26:39.280 --> 00:26:41.874
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:26:42.480 --> 00:26:44.710
- Thought you were going to cotillion.
- I thought you were.

00:26:44.880 --> 00:26:47.633
Yeah. No.

00:26:48.840 --> 00:26:50.831
Yeah, me neither.

00:26:51.600 --> 00:26:54.433
- Which one's sword?
- Not the one you're hitting.

00:26:54.600 --> 00:26:57.319
- Got it.
- Okay, now you're stabbing me.

00:26:57.480 --> 00:27:00.790
Just don't touch any of the buttons.
Follow me through the forest...

00:27:00.960 --> 00:27:03.713
...and maybe we'll both make it
out of here alive.

00:27:05.360 --> 00:27:07.715
So you didn't feel like going, huh?

00:27:07.880 --> 00:27:10.678
Yeah. No, not really for me.

00:27:10.840 --> 00:27:14.116
What? Waltzing and orchids?
What could be more you?

00:27:14.280 --> 00:27:16.191
Guess I don't really fit in, huh?

00:27:16.360 --> 00:27:18.590
Oh, I got news for you. Nobody does.

00:27:19.720 --> 00:27:23.508
I guarantee you every single person
at that cotillion feels like a fraud.

00:27:23.680 --> 00:27:27.389
They've all got secrets, and they're all
terrified the neighbors will find out.

00:27:28.240 --> 00:27:29.958
What's your secret?

00:27:31.040 --> 00:27:36.239
Sometimes, when the sun's
coming up and the surf is good...

00:27:36.400 --> 00:27:40.393
...and I haven't pissed my wife off
quite as much as I have today...

00:27:41.440 --> 00:27:43.237
...I kind of like this place.

00:27:44.920 --> 00:27:46.592
You just stabbed me again.

00:27:47.560 --> 00:27:48.788
Sorry.

00:27:48.960 --> 00:27:50.473
I can't believe you're not coming.

00:27:50.640 --> 00:27:55.236
It's just after the whole Luke and Ryan
thing last night, I don't feel...

00:27:55.400 --> 00:27:56.753
Coop...

00:27:56.920 --> 00:27:58.194
...Ryan isn't even here.

00:27:58.520 --> 00:27:59.873
He's not?

00:28:00.840 --> 00:28:03.070
Yeah, well, even so.

00:28:03.720 --> 00:28:05.039
I'm just not up for it.

00:28:07.920 --> 00:28:09.558
She's not coming.

00:28:10.920 --> 00:28:12.990
So, what did I get all dressed up for?

00:28:24.920 --> 00:28:28.117
I mean, whatever you think about
the whole superhero movie genre...

00:28:28.280 --> 00:28:30.794
...at least people are now reading
the source material.

00:28:30.960 --> 00:28:35.476
I cannot believe that you read
comic books. I mean, you're a girl.

00:28:35.640 --> 00:28:38.518
What's that supposed to mean?
And I call them "graphic novels."

00:28:38.680 --> 00:28:42.116
In fact, if more people did, maybe
the form wouldn't be so marginalized.

00:28:42.280 --> 00:28:44.191
I couldn't agree more.

00:28:45.680 --> 00:28:48.672
Summer, are you ready?
You look just great.

00:28:48.840 --> 00:28:50.319
So listen...

00:28:55.840 --> 00:28:57.432
You...

00:28:58.080 --> 00:28:59.832
...found another date.
- Yeah.

00:29:00.000 --> 00:29:02.912
It's kind of an emergency,
but you're off the hook.

00:29:04.120 --> 00:29:06.714
- Sorry.
- No, that's...

00:29:10.680 --> 00:29:12.352
That's fine.

00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:29.029
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:29:30.960 --> 00:29:32.188
You're not at cotillion.

00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:34.188
Neither are you.

00:29:37.520 --> 00:29:40.990
Look, I hope you didn't not go
because of last night or...

00:29:41.400 --> 00:29:42.913
...because of me.

00:29:45.280 --> 00:29:46.633
How come you're not going?

00:29:50.280 --> 00:29:53.477
So you think hiding out, staying home
is gonna make everything better?

00:29:54.160 --> 00:29:56.435
Seems to be working for you.

00:29:59.480 --> 00:30:01.675
I'll go if you go.

00:30:03.400 --> 00:30:07.234
Ryan, come on. Check this out. I have
totally annihilated all the other ninjas.

00:30:07.400 --> 00:30:09.152
I'm already on to the...

00:30:09.640 --> 00:30:11.278
Marissa. Hello.

00:30:11.720 --> 00:30:13.199
Hey.

00:30:13.960 --> 00:30:15.598
So we're gonna go.

00:30:16.600 --> 00:30:17.794
To cotillion.

00:30:21.720 --> 00:30:22.789
I'll get the car.

00:30:27.720 --> 00:30:30.075
Hey, Jimmy, there you are.

00:30:30.240 --> 00:30:33.312
- Greg, how you doing?
- I'll be better once I get that check...

00:30:33.480 --> 00:30:36.313
...get this property deal closed,
get my wife off my back.

00:30:36.480 --> 00:30:39.597
- I don't have it.
- What do you mean? Did you forget it?

00:30:39.760 --> 00:30:43.594
This isn't the time or place. Stop by the
office tomorrow, and we'll talk about it.

00:30:43.760 --> 00:30:45.830
Talk about it? Talk about what?

00:30:52.400 --> 00:30:55.153
- Excuse me.
- Jimmy...

00:30:57.800 --> 00:30:59.870
I don't believe it.

00:31:04.560 --> 00:31:07.791
You told Summer you weren't coming.
Now you're here with him?

00:31:07.960 --> 00:31:10.349
- Ryan and I aren't here together.
- I'm not an idiot.

00:31:10.520 --> 00:31:12.511
Then listen to her
and stop acting like one.

00:31:12.680 --> 00:31:14.272
What did you say?

00:31:14.800 --> 00:31:17.712
- Forget it.
- No, what did you say? Come on, man.

00:31:17.880 --> 00:31:19.393
Luke, stop it.

00:31:22.840 --> 00:31:25.400
I'm over this. We're done.

00:31:43.880 --> 00:31:46.678
Hey, look who decided to show up.

00:31:46.840 --> 00:31:50.196
Don't worry, your hit man already
took care of it. I didn't feel a thing.

00:31:50.760 --> 00:31:52.239
I'm here now, if you want to...

00:31:52.840 --> 00:31:55.434
No, too late. You missed your shot.

00:31:55.600 --> 00:31:59.195
I guess you'll have to go
with Princess Mononoke over there.

00:32:00.440 --> 00:32:04.035
- And what are you gonna do?
- Oh, so now you care? Go.

00:32:05.800 --> 00:32:09.315
Marissa, if you'd just stuck
to the original plan...

00:32:10.400 --> 00:32:13.119
- Sorry. Do you want Daddy to go find...?
- No, Mom.

00:32:13.280 --> 00:32:17.034
- You can't debut without an escort.
- I hear there's a white knight available.

00:32:19.600 --> 00:32:23.513
Well, that's very nice of you to offer,
but I don't think it's appropriate.

00:32:23.680 --> 00:32:25.272
I'll go get dressed.

00:32:33.400 --> 00:32:35.436
Could you be any more pathetic?

00:32:35.840 --> 00:32:37.990
A Ione figure sitting on the floor...

00:32:38.160 --> 00:32:41.072
...wondering if he'll be Ionely
for the rest of his life.

00:32:41.640 --> 00:32:44.200
Hey, your sensitivity, it's really...

00:32:44.360 --> 00:32:47.750
...nonexistent.
- You know what your problem is?

00:32:48.840 --> 00:32:50.956
You're not a man.

00:32:51.120 --> 00:32:53.031
Again, not appreciating
the brutal honesty.

00:32:53.200 --> 00:32:54.952
Do you know what girls find sexy?

00:32:55.120 --> 00:32:57.554
Nope. Wait, let me guess.

00:32:57.720 --> 00:33:01.998
- Dudes who play water polo.
- Confidence. Watch this.

00:33:03.520 --> 00:33:05.909
- Seth?
- Yes?

00:33:06.080 --> 00:33:08.594
I don't have a date to the cotillion.

00:33:09.120 --> 00:33:10.917
Would you be my escort?

00:33:12.560 --> 00:33:14.278
I mean...

00:33:14.440 --> 00:33:16.954
Confidence, Cohen.

00:33:18.800 --> 00:33:20.870
Let's do this.

00:33:21.040 --> 00:33:25.795
Hair's good, makeup's good. Very nice.
Stand up straight. Gum, please.

00:33:25.960 --> 00:33:26.949
How did this happen?

00:33:27.120 --> 00:33:30.317
How did I go from having three dates
to cotillion to having none?

00:33:30.480 --> 00:33:32.835
I'm sorry, girl. That blows.

00:33:36.360 --> 00:33:38.157
Good news. I'm available again.

00:33:38.600 --> 00:33:40.113
You are?

00:33:42.960 --> 00:33:46.077
No. No. We're gonna go this way. No.

00:33:57.000 --> 00:34:00.072
Five hundred channels and nothing on.

00:34:01.080 --> 00:34:03.275
You couldn't put on a tux?

00:34:03.440 --> 00:34:05.829
Pick your battles, honey.

00:34:06.480 --> 00:34:08.357
Good evening, everyone.

00:34:08.520 --> 00:34:14.470
And welcome to the 47th annual
Newport Beach Debutante Cotillion.

00:34:22.480 --> 00:34:23.754
Hey.

00:34:26.080 --> 00:34:27.991
Are you ready to make your debut?

00:34:33.760 --> 00:34:37.878
Holly Fisher,
daughter of Greg and Marianne Fisher.

00:34:47.560 --> 00:34:51.951
Anna Stern,
daughter of Cameron and Patricia Stern.

00:35:05.960 --> 00:35:10.272
Marissa Cooper,
daughter of James and Julie Cooper.

00:35:12.200 --> 00:35:15.272
- I love you, kiddo.
- I love you too, Daddy.

00:35:43.360 --> 00:35:44.839
And now, ladies and gentlemen...

00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:49.357
...please join me in congratulating
this year's debutantes.

00:36:29.040 --> 00:36:30.996
We never finished our conversation.

00:36:31.160 --> 00:36:33.390
I gotta tell you,
you got me a little concerned.

00:36:33.560 --> 00:36:36.757
Believe me, it's nothing
that can't wait until tomorrow.

00:36:37.880 --> 00:36:39.472
Don't the girls look beautiful?

00:36:40.120 --> 00:36:41.997
I hate dancing.

00:36:42.160 --> 00:36:43.309
Thanks.

00:36:43.480 --> 00:36:46.153
No, with you, it's...

00:36:46.320 --> 00:36:48.356
It's not horrible.

00:36:48.880 --> 00:36:50.632
You're sweet.

00:36:50.800 --> 00:36:54.315
- Are you leading?
- I'm trying.

00:36:54.480 --> 00:36:57.153
Attitude. I like that.

00:36:57.320 --> 00:37:00.915
I've put in an offer. I got a mortgage,
the kids are in private school.

00:37:01.080 --> 00:37:02.877
If there's a problem, I need to know.

00:37:03.040 --> 00:37:05.110
Now is not the time.

00:37:06.200 --> 00:37:07.349
Jimmy, where's my money?

00:37:08.480 --> 00:37:10.311
I asked you a question.
Where's my money?

00:37:10.480 --> 00:37:13.199
I didn't want you to find out
this way, but I don't have it.

00:37:13.360 --> 00:37:15.430
- What?
- I will, but I don't have it right now.

00:37:15.600 --> 00:37:18.273
- Lf you don't have my money, who does?
- Hey, look.

00:37:20.360 --> 00:37:23.750
I promise I'm working on it, all right?
There's been some bad investments.

00:37:23.920 --> 00:37:25.751
Are you telling me you lost everything?

00:37:26.160 --> 00:37:27.593
Would you just keep it down?

00:37:27.760 --> 00:37:31.275
I won't keep it down. That is my money.
My retirement, my kids' tuition!

00:37:31.440 --> 00:37:33.829
- I'm sorry.
- Son of a bitch!

00:37:34.880 --> 00:37:38.555
- Oh, my God.
- You're a thief! You took my money!

00:37:38.720 --> 00:37:39.994
Greg!

00:37:40.880 --> 00:37:43.678
I want my money back, you hear me?

00:37:43.880 --> 00:37:45.598
Get off me!

00:37:45.880 --> 00:37:47.871
You're a thief! You're a thief!

00:37:48.080 --> 00:37:49.195
- Get off me.
- Go outside.

00:37:49.360 --> 00:37:51.430
- He's a thief! You're a thief!
- Leave. Please.

00:37:51.600 --> 00:37:52.749
- Come on.
- He's a thief!

00:37:52.920 --> 00:37:54.433
Dad!

00:37:54.600 --> 00:37:56.272
Take it outside. Come on.

00:38:02.600 --> 00:38:04.397
I haven't seen you
in a fight since...

00:38:04.560 --> 00:38:06.676
...ever.
- Now you know why.

00:38:06.840 --> 00:38:09.593
What are you talking about?
He sucker-punched you.

00:38:10.520 --> 00:38:13.671
You didn't have to jump in like that,
defend Jimmy.

00:38:13.840 --> 00:38:16.070
Well, I've always had this thing
for the underdog.

00:38:17.280 --> 00:38:22.274
After I fill out the police report, maybe
we should go and see how he's doing.

00:38:23.640 --> 00:38:25.198
Hi.

00:38:27.320 --> 00:38:30.630
So, sorry. I know I promised
I wouldn't get into any fights.

00:38:30.800 --> 00:38:33.473
We can make an exception
in this case.

00:38:33.640 --> 00:38:37.315
The police, however, will have questions.
As your attorney, I advise you...

00:38:38.080 --> 00:38:40.594
...get out of here.
- Thanks.

00:38:43.800 --> 00:38:45.199
Hey.

00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:50.158
You don't mind if I walk
your date home, do you?

00:38:52.360 --> 00:38:53.952
- No.
- Cool.

00:38:54.120 --> 00:38:57.999
That's quite a debut you had tonight.
You know how to present yourself.

00:38:58.160 --> 00:39:00.913
Finally, a Cohen who can throw down.

00:39:01.080 --> 00:39:02.638
You wanna come with us?

00:39:03.600 --> 00:39:06.512
- I'll just see you at home.
- See you at home.

00:39:11.640 --> 00:39:14.950
So do you think
that I'll get to see you again?

00:39:15.840 --> 00:39:17.910
- No.
- Okay.

00:39:18.080 --> 00:39:19.399
No, it's just...

00:39:19.560 --> 00:39:21.596
I know this might sound kind of...

00:39:21.760 --> 00:39:23.478
...whatever...

00:39:23.640 --> 00:39:26.438
...but I'm spending the rest
of the summer on a sailing trip.

00:39:26.600 --> 00:39:28.716
To Tahiti.

00:39:28.880 --> 00:39:32.077
- You like sailing?
- Yeah.

00:40:10.840 --> 00:40:12.478
You okay?

00:40:15.440 --> 00:40:17.351
What happened in there?

00:40:19.600 --> 00:40:21.352
I don't know.

00:40:23.000 --> 00:40:25.150
What's gonna happen now?

00:40:29.840 --> 00:40:31.319
I don't know.

00:40:37.480 --> 00:40:39.311
Come on, let's go.

00:40:40.880 --> 00:40:42.199
Come on.

00:40:49.600 --> 00:40:50.953
Came as soon as I heard.

00:40:55.440 --> 00:40:57.112
Are you...?

00:41:00.840 --> 00:41:02.353
I'm sorry.

00:41:04.280 --> 00:41:06.510
Can I take you home?

00:41:08.240 --> 00:41:10.754
- We could talk, maybe.
- I...

00:41:11.440 --> 00:41:13.317
I just need to be alone right now.

00:41:16.880 --> 00:41:18.313
Thanks.

